"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code incorrectly uses library Matplotlib. The issue lies in lines 19 and 20. When using a DateFormatter and a MonthLocator, you should not manually set the xticks and xticklabels. The DateFormatter and MonthLocator are designed to automatically format and locate the ticks on the x-axis. Manually setting the xticks and xticklabels can cause the ticks to overlap or not be properly formatted.\",\n  \"patch\": \"19,20c19\\n< ax.set_xticks(df.date.unique())\\n< ax.set_xticklabels(labels=df.date.unique(), rotation=45)\\n---\\n> fig.autofmt_xdate(rotation=45)\"\n}"